<p>The <b>Big Lie</b> (<a href="/wiki/German_language" title="German language">German</a>: <span lang="de" xml:lang="de"><i>Große Lüge</i></span>) is a <a href="/wiki/Propaganda" title="Propaganda">propaganda</a> technique. It was defined by <a href="/wiki/Adolf_Hitler" title="Adolf Hitler">Adolf Hitler</a> in his 1925 autobiography <i><a href="/wiki/Mein_Kampf" title="Mein Kampf">Mein Kampf</a></i> as a lie so "colossal" that no one would believe that someone "could have the impudence to distort the truth so infamously".</p>
